      <h3>Jonathan Glass - the Artist</h3>
        <p>
          Jonathan took pastel and figurative studies from ages 10-18. He considers his passion to have started in his third year of college. Teacher Alan E. Cober taught journaling of experiences through sketchbook class. This was informative to develop his personal style of drawing.
        </p>
        <p>
          While Jonathan's grounding started with Cober, he continued to reconcile his notion of impermanence with jazz sketches. Some noted musicians have played at his openings. Some have sat for portratis in his studio (ie. Ravi Coltrane, Dan Tepfer, etc).
        </p>
        <p>
          The most important thing to his art is that whether painting or drawing, there has to be an element of improvisation, as well. Jonathan hopes that he could in some small way link the continuity of jazz from greats of the be-bop era to the standard bearers and hard boppers to avant-garde jazz and the beginnings of fusion and hip-hop.
